    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "**Describe the bug**\r\n`cython -3a` command generates C code in html file which is rendered to single line:\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n**To Reproduce**\r\nCode to reproduce the behaviour:\r\n```cython\r\ncdef int a = 3\r\ncdef int b = 5\r\n\r\nprint(a * b)\r\n```\r\n![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/827060/182687499-82a05ced-c51f-49b0-992d-c07a7de03ebc.png)\r\n\r\n\r\n**Expected behavior**\r\nC code rendered in browser should be splited into several lines\r\n\r\n**Environment (please complete the following information):**\r\n - OS: Any\r\n - Python version 3.9\r\n - Cython version master\r\n\r\n**Additional context**\r\nIssue was introduced by following commit:\r\n```\r\ncommit 0b4370678e5b00a020cd990f922964d3aba59884\r\nAuthor: Stefan Behnel <stefan_ml@behnel.de>\r\nDate:   Sat Jul 16 22:14:48 2022 +0200\r\n\r\n    Reduce overhead in the code writer when writing out simple code without newlines.\r\n\r\n Cython/Compiler/Code.pxd |  1 +\r\n Cython/Compiler/Code.py  | 19 ++++++++++++-------\r\n```",
